   <mods:abstract>Congratulates John Jay on appointment and safe arrival. John Jay may be
            able to defeat schemes of "designing men" without "property or money" who would bring
            downfall of order and government. Describes late disturbances in Britain. The danger
            that threatens religion, judicature, juries, all Government. La Fayette last write him
            but 6 days before he left the French Army. Laments that LaFayette's plan was not
            followed in France--"France would now have been a Happy and great Nation." For 9 months
            has not heard from daughter, wife of Swedish Consul in Marseilles. Asks John Jay to make
            discreet inquiries as to her and her children through American Consuls in
            France.</mods:abstract>
